<DATELINE>SANTA MONICA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two bandits who robbed Los Angeles
Dodgers slugger Kirk Gibson of money and a luxury car probably never
realized the celebrity status of their victim, police said.
   ``They hit a citizen who happened to be a baseball star,'' police
Sgt. John Miehle said. ``It was just a random deal.''
   The outfielder and his wife were followed to their home in Santa
Monica and held up early Thursday morning by a gunman and an
accomplice. Gibson handed over about $500 and his keys to one of the
robbers, who then fled in the baseball star's 1988 blue BMW.
   No arrests had been made by Friday.
   Gibson, 32, the National League's Most Valuable Player last year,
and his 31-year-old wife, Joann, were unharmed.
