<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--KlanRally     07-01 0161</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Klan Rally,0164</SECOND>
<HEAD>Tiny Klan Rally Draws 600 Counter Demonstrators</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FREDERICK, Md. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   More than 600 people threw rocks and
heckled three dozen white-robed Klansmen Saturday as they assembled
for a rally in a downtown park.
   Members of Frederick Citizens Against the Klan and the African
People's Socialist Party shouted anti-racist slogans at the Klan
group, who carried billy clubs and American and Confederate flags.
   The protesters booed and chanted, drowning out a speech by
Maryland KKK Grand Dragon Roger Kelly. One man held up a tape
recorder that was blaring the Rev. Martin Luther King Jr.'s famous
``I have a dream ...'' speech.
   Hundreds of people were on the Klansmen's heels as they left the
park. Amid shouting and pushing, the Klansmen hopped in the back of
a U-Haul truck, which was pelted with rocks as it pulled away.
   A woman in the crowd was hit with a rock. She was treated at a
local hospital and released.
</TEXT>
